  <channel>
    <title>Oceans contributor: Michael Vardon</title>
    <description>Michael Vardon is an expert in environmental accounting and has been collecting and analyzing data for more than 20 years. His initial studies and career focused on studies of animal population dynamics but his focus shifted when he moved to the Australian Bureau of Statistics in 2000, where he worked on wide range of environmental topics including land management, water and environmental accounting. He became director of the Centre of Environmental Accounting in 2005, a position he left in 2014. He is currently researching and teaching environmental accounting at the Australian National University.
</description>
